express-generator is a framework MVC 

To install : sudo npm install - g express-generator

to start project with template engine : ejs or hogan

-> express projectName --ejs 

it provide project structure like :

ProjectName
 |-package.json
 |-app.js or index.js or server.js
 |-->routes
 |----user.js
 |----employee.js
 |----product.js
 |-->model(DAO)
 |----user
 |----employee
 |----product
 |-->views
 |----userView.ejs
 |----error.ejs
 |-->public
 |



 MongoDB -> NoSQL
            Not Only Structured Query Language


    NoSQL VS  RDBMS

    RDBMS => SQL / PLSQL

    RDBMS ---> SELECT * FROM emp WHERE empID = 123

    NoSQL ---> db.emp.findOne({empID: 123});



ORACLE 
------------

ID      NAME        MARKS
2       ASSOUA      89


MongoDB : unstructured Database
   
   i.e : 

    [
        {
            "ID": 1,
            "NAME" : "ASSOUA",
            "MARKS" : 89
        }, 

        {
            "ID": 2,
            "NAME" : "manizan",
            
        }, 

    ]

i.e : 2

    [
        "book": {

            "title" : "",
            "author": "",
            "date" :  "",
            "feedback" : [
                {"userId" : 123, "comments": "blah blah "},
                {"userId" : 1, "comments": "I like this very much "}
            ]
        },

        "book" : {
            "title" : "",
            "author" : "",
            "date" : ""
        } 
    ]



    RDBMS       VS      MongoDB
    -----               --------
    Table               Collection
    Row                 Document
    Tuple               Field
    Rows and Columns    JSON 
    Schema is must      No Schema



    NodeJs can talk to MongoDb and MongoDB can talk to NodeJs

    Client         Server          DB
    UI    <------> NodeJs <------> MongoDB

    
    Download MongoDB Community Server

    After installed MongoDB

    MongoDB Compas (GUI)


    inside file installation we can find files:

    mongod : to launch instance of the server (double clic to execute)
    mongo  : to connect client to the instance (double clic to launch) or use mongo compass (it's a GUI client)


    DataBase: 

    To see all databases i,nstalled : show dbs
    To create ou to connect to one db : use nameOfDataBase
    To see Collection (table) : show collections

    To see data in collection : db.users.find().pretty() 


Connect  NodeJs to/from MongoDB

-> If you want to access only records for query MongoDBClient

-> ORM (Object Relationship Mapping ) mongoose
